  "title": "Business Analyst AB-013",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role: </strong>Business Analyst (User Task Activity for CoreBanking System Implementation)</p><p><strong>Job Requisition Number: </strong>AB-013</p><p><strong>Job Level: </strong>Minimum 6 years of Relevantexperience</p><p><strong>Location: </strong>Singapore</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Plan and lead the creation and revision of     banking operation procedures aligned with the new core banking system     implementation.</li><li>Develop detailed plans, documentation, and     progress management reports for user task procedures.</li><li>Coordinate with regional and branch-level     teams to ensure standardization of procedures while accommodating     branch-specific requirements.</li><li>Manage issues and progress for procedure     development activities.</li><li>Collaborate closely with stakeholders across     multiple branches and departments (Operations, Risk, Legal, Internal     Audit, etc.).</li><li>Ensure compliance and quality in procedure     documentation in line with banking standards and regulations.</li><li>Facilitate effective communication and     collaboration among physically remote teams across APAC.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor's degree in     any field.</li><li>Minimum 3 years of     experience in a consulting firm within the banking industry or on the     user/operations side of a bank.</li><li>Strong expertise in     document creation and logical thinking.</li><li>Proven experience in     creating, revising, reviewing, or approving banking operational procedures     (e.g., Operational Planning, Back Office, Risk Management, Legal, or     Internal Audit).</li><li>Strong interpersonal     and coordination skills, including remote and cross-border teams.</li><li>Knowledge of core     banking business flows and back-office operations, experience with major     banking systems such as Trade360 TPS, ACBS, GPP, FLEXCUBE, or GLCS and     managing small or distributed teams are a plus.</li></ul>",
